<TITLE> Ports on alert as Bay depression brews </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 15 (bdndews24.com)  The weather office asked maritime ports to be on alert as a depression was forming over the Bay of Bengal on Monday. Met department officer SM Mahmudul Haque told bdnews24.com that the maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla have been asked to keep hoisted local cautionary signal number 3. Fishing boats and trawlers have been asked to remain close to the shore and move with caution. bdnews2
